rities      Six Feet Apart: Stories from UIC during COVID-19                       Introduction     This guide presents information resources on the topic of COVID-19 and is intended for research purposes only . For official University of Illinois at Chicago updates, please visit the UIC Today Coronavirus Disease page.  For personal health questions:   UIC students - Student Health at University Village  UIC employees - University Health Service  Community members outside UIC - City of Chicago Information . See also For the Public .          Scientific Research      LitCovid  From the National Library of Medicine : LitCovid is a curated literature hub for tracking up-to-date scientific information about the 2019 novel Coronavirus.    COVID-evidence.org  A "continuously updated database of the worldwide available evidence on interventions for COVID-19," gathering publications, clinical trials, and preprints from multiple sources.    COVID-19 Best Evidence Front Door  From the University of Michigan, this portal searches "meta-analyses, literature syntheses, and clinical guideline documents from multiple highly-reliable sources via a single search."    PubMed search  Runs a pre-defined search in PubMed for relevant publications.    Medical Library Association COVID-19 Search Strategies     Clinical Trials search  Runs a pre-defined search for relevant clinical trials.    DisasterLit  The DisasterLit database provides access to "disaster medicine and public health documents available on the Internet at no cost." Search here for grey literature that you won't find in scholarly databases.    medRxiv COVID-19 SARS-CoV-2 preprints     GenBank - SARS-CoV-2 (Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2) Sequences     InfoDocket Coronavirus (COVID 19) Resources       Policy Research    COVID-19 Legal Research Resources       Open Access Resources  Many publishers are granting free access to COVID-19 research that normally would require paid subscriptions to access, including:    American National Standards Institute     DynaMed - COVID-19 (Novel Coronavirus)     Elsevier - Novel Coronavirus Information Center     Emerald Publishing - Coronavirus, the management of epidemics and the wider impact on society     JAMA Network - Coronavirus Resource Center     JPHMP (Journal of Public Health Management and Practice) Direct - COVID-19 Resources     The Lancet - COVID-19 Resource Centre     Mary Ann Liebert - Article collection     New England Journal of Medicine - Coronavirus (Covid-19)     Oxford - COVID-19 Evidence Service     ProQuest Coronavirus Research Database     Springer Nature - SARS-CoV-2 and COVID-19     Taylor & Francis - Coronavirus reading list     UpToDate - Coronavirus Disease 2019     Wiley Online Library - Novel Coronavirus               Next: UIC, Chicago, & Illinois >>          Last Updated:  Apr 30, 2020 2:43 PM    URL:  https://researchguides.uic.edu/coronavirus    Print Page     Staff Login          Tags:  covid-19                   Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations          Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Phone  (312) 996-2724              Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago    1750 W. Polk St.   Chicago , IL  60612       Circulation  (312) 996-8966    Reference  (312) 996-9163              Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria    One Illini Drive PO Box 1649   Peoria , IL  61656       Phone  (309) 671-8490              Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford    1601 Parkview Ave.   Rockford , IL  61107       Phone  (815) 395-5650              Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana    102 Medical Sciences Building, 506 S. Mathews   Urbana , IL  61801       Circulation  (217) 333-4893    Reference  (217) 244-0607             Faculty services    Alumni services    Distance student services    Accessibility services     Social Networking             © 2016 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois  Priv